The paper discusses the vulnerability of locally differentially private protocols to adversarial manipulation, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the accuracy and efficiency of these protocols, which are important topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of cryptographic techniques, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SI).
